1.30pm: Good morning afternoon and welcome back to the first ever day-night Test. 9.25 pm The first day of day-night Test cricket has come to an end. Twelve wickets have fallen, but presumably not because the ball couldn't be seen properly. The ball hasn't had to be changed either, so its durability has held up so far. More than 47,000 people have come to watch at Adelaide Oval, though there is the novelty value. All in all, I think it works, though it might be too early to tell.

New Zealand chose to bat and were dismissed far too early for their liking. Definitely Australia's day, though they too lost two wickets before stumps. The major worry for the hosts, though, is the fitness of Mitchell Starc, who left the field with ankle trouble.
